&lt;p&gt;The financial infrastructure team at Vercel builds the critical billing systems and delightful user experiences that power pricing, subscriptions, and revenue operations across all Vercel products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re seeking engineers to join a team that&#39;s central to Vercel&#39;s business strategy and growth. In this role, you&#39;ll architect and develop scalable usage-based billing platforms, spend management systems, entitlements, and usage forecasting that directly enable our company&#39;s expansion. You&#39;ll collaborate with engineering teams across the entire stack—from v0 to Infrastructure—to build a platform that every team at Vercel depends on.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is your opportunity to reimagine billing experiences for both enterprise clients and millions of individual developers, working on systems that process significant transaction volumes. Your code will handle mission-critical financial operations that keep our business running and build trust with our customers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect and build the next generation of billing and monetization systems that reaches millions of users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop robust and scalable billing APIs and services, commercializing all Vercel products and offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop tools that empower internal teams to seamlessly incorporate billing workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously optimize systems&#39; performance and reliability to ensure a frictionless user experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with a wide array of stakeholders, including the Product, Data, Finance, and Go-To-Market teams, as well as engineers across several teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess at least 6+ years of experience in full-stack development with added experience in critical systems like payments, billing, or monetization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled in server-side languages such as Node.js, Python, or Go, with a proven track record of implementing complex business logic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with cloud platforms and containerization technologies like AWS and Docker&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate a passion for delivering high-quality code, with particular emphasis on accuracy, security, and scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exhibit excellent problem-solving abilities and effective communication skills, especially when collaborating with diverse teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoy engaging with various partners, particularly those outside of engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
